		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Thomas</placeName> <date>26<hi rend="sup">th</hi> December 1861</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Revd &#38; dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">I read with much plea&#8222;<lb/>&#8222;sure your issue of Povbr<add>&#63;</add> a p&#44; and as I am interested in<lb/> <persName>P&#39;s</persName> letter I beg to thank you for its publication.  I regret<lb/> to say that our <persName>Revd Mr. M</persName> has not escaped the fate of<lb/> most good men and his good intentions and honest perseverance<lb/> are doubted by a <sic>handfull</sic> of his congregation&#44; thanks to<lb/> God it is the worst judging portion&#44; still they may influence<lb/> enemies against him in countries where they are not known.<lb/>  Therefore as eulogions<add>&#63;</add> have appeared in your paper in his favor<lb/> and his <sic>entagonist</sic> may select the same field to attack him<lb/> I address you these few lines&#44; as it were to put you on your<lb/> guard&#59; I am aware that the principle under which you<lb/> conduct your valuable &#38; much esteemed Occident&#44; is to allow<lb/> free discussions&#44; but I am certain when those discussions aim to<lb/> destroy the reputation of a faithful servant of <placeName>Israel&#39;s</placeName> God you<lb/> will know with what contempt to treat them&#44; and not lend<lb/> your periodical to such purposes.  I inform you this much<lb/> that you may know in case you are addressed&#44; otherwise please<lb/> not to mention anything to the public&#44; as I wish not to be the<lb/> means of exposing any little difficulties which may exist among<lb/> us.  <persName>Mr Myers</persName> friends are the most respectable members of<lb/> his congregation&#44; besides I am happy to say he enjoys the esteem<lb/> of the whole community&#44; <persName>N&#39;s</persName> letter therefore expressed the views</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>of a respectable majority.</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">I am respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">Yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">MDAsorio</persName></p>
		</body>
	</text>
